DAEWORK
=======

C++ http daemon server framework library

INSTALATION

Building on Unix with git, gcc and autotools

Home page for daewrok:
  http://www.daework.com

Prerequisites:
	g++ (or another C++ compiler)
        make
	libtool

If you want to use a not release tarball, you'll also need:
	autoconf (autoreconf)
	automake

Make sure you have a complete libtool install, including libtoolize

Github repo for daework:
  https://github.com/fernancoder/DaeWork

    $ git clone https://github.com/fernancoder/DaeWork.git

This project is divided into a main module and several sub-modules that are compiled independently. Main module includes the DaeWork framework. Secondary modules provides access to services like mySql, MongoDB, Memcached or RabitMQ.

To install DaeWork:

    $ cd DaeWork

Then 

    $ ./configure
    $ make
    $ sudo make install

To run the test program execute:

    $ cd demo
    $ test -c test.ini

    Enter "http://localhost:2021/?action=test&name=your_name" URL in your browser

To install a module, first you must display the available:

    $ cd modules/
    $ ls -l

Then
    $ cd [module-name]
    $ make
    $ sudo make install


